title: Refactored hardwareStepCounter
message:
Refactored hardwareStepCounter

The HardwareStepCounterService now extends the AbstractStepDetectorService and can be handled like every other implementation.
The only difference is that the StepCounter kills itself after receiving the sensor data.

title: values-de: use "gehen" instead of "laufen"
message:
values-de: use "gehen" instead of "laufen"

The use of "laufen" is ambiguous, since it can mean both "walking"
(only in colloquial speech[1], and even then, only in certain
regions[2]) and "running".

[1] http://www.duden.de/rechtschreibung/laufen
[2] https://de.wiktionary.org/wiki/laufen
